Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Display
    This class is used to display the content of the odometer variables (x, y, theta).
    LightLocalizer
    This class contains methods that are responsible for performing light localization at the current position of the robot
    Main
    The main driver class for the search and rescue procedure.
    Navigation
    This class is primarily responsible for the navigation of the robot to the island from its starting zone, it is also responsible for the navigation of the robot to its starting zone from the island.
    Object
    This class is responsible for differentiating between an obstacle and a stranded vehicle.
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) position.
    Reading
    Class to hold a basic value object coming from the US sensor.
    Resources
    This class is used to define static resources in one place for easy access and to avoid cluttering the rest of the codebase.
    Sensors
    This class is responsible for running the 3 colour sensors and the ultrasonic sensor in threads and storing the data returned by each sensor.
    StrandedVehicle
    This class is responsible for detecting the vertical pin of the stranded vehicle and eventually lifting the stranded vehicle
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    Class to manage and record values of the ultrasonic sensor.
